        public T set(java.lang.Integer aKey,
             T aValue)
        Description copied from interface: Aggregate
        Associates aValue or null to an element of this aggregation. Whether the element is created, modified, or removed is not defined by this interface.

        Sub-interfaces or implementations may throw exceptions in addition to those specified here.

        Specified by:
        set in interface Aggregate<java.lang.Integer,T>
        Parameters:
        aKey - The element's key. When a non-null key would be added to the key set then keys().getElementType().isInstance(aKey) must answer true. This interfaces doesn't specify whether a null key is allowed.
        aValue - The element's value or null. getElementType().isInstance(aValue) must answer true for a non-null value.
        Returns:
        The prior value held by the element when applicable or null when not.
